Keeping in view that online teaching is new to everyone,
and we need to learn while delivering, like an entrepreneur, 
a two day workshop on "Online Teaching: Challenges and Opportunitites" 
has been organised by Department of Civil Engineering, 
Guru Nanak Dev Engineering College, Ludhiana, from Spetember 09-10, 2020.
The prime objective of workshop is to share our experience,
difficulties encountered and any innovation done,
with hope that sharing will benefit all others. 

Session on day 01 started with Dr H.S. Rai's comment 
about Engineering faculty not being trained for online 
as well as offline teaching as none has been qualified with a B.Ed or M.Ed degree.
But, due to exposure to  by acquiring technical education and experience over time, engineering faculty
has proved and served till now.

